&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chandrika Pujari; 51kg.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indian boxers won a total of five medals at the World Boxing Futures Cup 2026 in Bangkok, Thailand.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gold Medalist:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Chandrika Pujari&lt;/strong&gt; won the gold in the Women&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;51kg&lt;/strong&gt; Division by defeating Uzbekistan&amp;rsquo;s Mardonova Nazokat.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Silver Medalists:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Gunjan&lt;/strong&gt; (48kg), &lt;strong&gt;Joyshree Devi&lt;/strong&gt; (54kg), and &lt;strong&gt;Ambekar Meetei&lt;/strong&gt; (Men&amp;rsquo;s 50kg) all secured silver medals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bronze Medalist:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Radhamani Longjam&lt;/strong&gt; (57kg) earned a bronze medal in the tournament.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Olympic Pathway:&lt;/strong&gt; This tournament serves as a key qualification event for the &lt;strong&gt;Dakar 2026 Youth Olympic Games&lt;/strong&gt; in Senegal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Youth Olympic Games (YOG)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The 2026 Summer Youth Olympics will be held in Dakar, Senegal, marking the first time an Olympic event will be held on the African continent.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Best International Cricketer (Women).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI)&amp;nbsp;organized the Naman Awards 2026 in New Delhi to felicitate top performers and World Cup-winning teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double Honor:&lt;/strong&gt; Smriti Mandhana was recognized as the &lt;strong&gt;Best International Cricketer (Women)&lt;/strong&gt; and also as the &lt;strong&gt;Highest Run Getter in ODIs (Women)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Men&amp;#39;s Counterpart:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;Polly Umrigar Award&lt;/strong&gt; (Best International Cricketer - Men) was awarded to &lt;strong&gt;Shubman Gill&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifetime Achievement:&lt;/strong&gt; The Col. C.K. Nayudu Lifetime Achievement Award was presented to &lt;strong&gt;Rahul Dravid&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Roger Binny&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Celebration:&lt;/strong&gt; The ceremony honored five World Cup/Champions Trophy winning teams, including the Women&amp;#39;s team led by &lt;strong&gt;Harmanpreet Kaur&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;BCCI Naman Awards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These are the annual awards given by the Board of Control for Cricket in India to recognize the consistent performances of Indian cricketers in both domestic and international circuits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Polly Umrigar Award&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Named after the legendary Indian captain, it is the highest honor for an active male international cricketer in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

