&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rahul Dravid and Roger Binny.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BCCI felicitated cricket legends and current stars at the Naman Awards 2026 in New Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lifetime Achievement:&lt;/strong&gt; The prestigious &lt;strong&gt;Col. C.K. Nayudu Lifetime Achievement Award&lt;/strong&gt; was jointly awarded to &lt;strong&gt;Rahul Dravid&lt;/strong&gt; (former India Captain and Coach) and &lt;strong&gt;Roger Binny&lt;/strong&gt; (1983 World Cup hero and current BCCI President).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Women&amp;#39;s Lifetime Award:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Mithali Raj&lt;/strong&gt; was honored with the &lt;strong&gt;BCCI Lifetime Achievement Award (Women)&lt;/strong&gt; for her historic contribution to the game.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Major Winners:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Shubman Gill&lt;/strong&gt; received the Polly Umrigar Award, while &lt;strong&gt;Smriti Mandhana&lt;/strong&gt; was named the Best International Cricketer (Women).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Recognition:&lt;/strong&gt; The BCCI also celebrated five World Cup-winning teams from the 2025-26 period.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Col. C.K. Nayudu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The award is named after India&amp;#39;s first Test captain. It is the highest honor bestowed by the BCCI upon a former player for their unparalleled contribution to Indian cricket.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

